Or the term “dear departed” signifies that, in his mind, she is already dead or as good as dead.

He must now either satisfy his unappetizing bride or find a plausible excuse to say good night and go to bed (the “original version”).

His access to the girl remains as problematic as ever.

The “charlatans” are the pharmacists whose potion he did not buy;

the pharmacist